      "message": "OK, so seems to work:\n\ndrawAtlas(..., {B, C})\ndrawAtlas(..., {filter, mpmap})\n// These give the default: filter:linear, mipmap:none\ndrawAtlas(..., null)  \ndrawAtlas(...)\n\nSince we are accepting a union, what should we do if the supplied parameter has all 4 known fields?\ne.g. {B, C, filter, mipmap}\n\nAs coded, since I search for \"cubic\" first, we will take that one. Should we just document this?\n\nRelated: what if a field is specified, but is null? I don\u0027t check for that today, since I just ask\n   if ([\u0027B\u0027] in sampling)\n\nOptions:\n- leave as is, and it will throw an exception if null\n- explicitly check for non-null, and treat null the same as not-present\n- other\n\nI know this is getting drawn out, but what we decide here can/should be applied to a slew of previous cases, so I want to really like this new pattern: (e.g. drawImage, drawImageRect, makeShader, etc.)\n",
